value.0: (An image of a hooded man in tattered Sith battle-garb flickers to life. The man glares at you with a defensive posture.)
You may call me Darth Validious...

(The image of the man flickers as he repeats himself.) 
Darth Validious. Do not make me repeat myself again.
I was an Inquisitor... Though that is the past.
I allowed my passion to take another form besides hate. . .
A young woman, strong in the force, caught my attention. She sought to abondon traditional teachings, I accompanied her.

(The man folds his arms.) 
As an Inquisitor, it was my duty to apprehend her or eliminate her. Instead, I allowed myself to care for her, some might say a foolish mistake. . . Perhaps it was. . . We were ambushed leaving our safe haven.
A fool. . . Possibly, but you can learn from my mistakes.

Do not allow yourself to become compromised. Do not become weak. Had I not allowed become infatuated with her, I would have seen the ambusing coming. Though, I would not have been in that situation at all.
Take heed of what I have said. There is nothing else for you here. (The man waves his hand and you feel yourself transported away.)
We were overpowered. Though she was quite adept in the ways of the Force and myself just as much with a Lightsaber, we were no match for their numbers.
I was beaten, tortured, I had my legs forcefully removed, and my connection to the force was stripped from me.
(The man reaches into his hood, grasping his forehead in pain.) The only solution I had was to have Force Sensitivie leeches placed into my brain. . . It works. . . Though it has its drawbacks. . .
(The image flickers and disappears momentarily before the man appears again. He is now adorned in pristine Inquisitor robes.)

(The man pulls his hood back over his head. He tenses his body, drawing dark energy.) I have banished my former essence here, as you have met. . .  That weakness has no place amongst the Inquisitorious.
It is time for you to leave
This is MY DOMAIN! I AM THE GRAND INQUISITOR AND I COMMAND YOU TO LEAVE!!
Very well (The man waves his hand as he fades away.)
Very well (The man waves his hand as he fades away.)
I apologize m'lord. Who were you?
